" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 15, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104kia1665702915819.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kia1665702915819.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kia1665702915819.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"kia1665702915819\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Describes the relationship between two tables.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kia1665702915819__section_arf_lbr_dwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d991638e50\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kia1665702915819__p_d129728e1_d129729e1_d129730e1\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">RelationshipType</code> structure is\n        used to describe a relationship. The relations of a table are described in lists of these\n        structures. These lists are available through the <code class=\"ph codeph\">RelationshipInfoType</code>\n        structure.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">Data type definitions are available in <code class=\"ph codeph\"><strong class=\"ph b\">unidbm.h</strong></code> located in the\n            <code class=\"ph codeph\"><strong class=\"ph b\">UnifaceAPSInstallDir\\uniface\\3gl\\include</strong></code> directory.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Elements</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__1\">Type </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__2\">Element </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__3\">Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">unsigned char</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">*RelationshipName</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__3\">Null-terminated name of the relationship (defined by\n                the user). </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">unsigned char</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">*OneModelName</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__3\">Name of the application model in which the one entity\n                resides.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">unsigned char</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">*ManyModelName</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__3\">Name of the application model in which the many entity\n                resides. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">unsigned char</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">*RelatedEntityName</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__3\">Name of the related entity, as defined in the\n                application model, that is, before entity assignment </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">unsigned char</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">*RelatedTableName</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__3\">Name of the related table after entity assignment.\n                This name can contain the full operating system file name. The connector must parse\n                the name, in the same way it does with <code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;uname</code> in modes 0,\n                1 and 2. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">int</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">IsOverflow</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__3\">When <code class=\"ph codeph\">IsOverflow</code> has the value 1, it\n                is a relation between a table and its overflow table. In other cases it has the\n                value 0.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">int</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">KeyNumber</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__3\">Uniface index number of the referenced key in the one\n                table. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">KeyTypeType</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">KeyType</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__3\">Type of referenced key in the one table. <p class=\"p\">The used\n                  data type <code class=\"ph codeph\">KeyTypeType</code> has the following definition:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"kia1665702915819__pre_pnc_nbr_dwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">typedef enum\n{\nPRIMARY_KEY,\nCANDIDATE_KEY\n} KeyTypeType;\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">int</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">RIFields</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__3\">Number of fields in the foreign key and in the\n                referenced key. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">int</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">*RIFieldNumberList</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__3\">Array of <code class=\"ph codeph\">RIFields</code> field numbers.\n                These identify the fields in the key (primary, candidate or foreign) of the current\n                table in the relationship (that is, the table which is described by the current\n                control block). </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">unsigned char</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">**RIFieldNameList</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__3\">Array of ‘RIFields’ pointers to null-terminated field\n                names. These identify the fields in the key (primary, candidate or foreign) of the\n                related table in the relationship (that is, the table which is not described by the\n                current control block). </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">ForeignKeyRuleType</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">OnDelete</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"kia1665702915819__table_d15422e1_d15423e1_d15424e1__entry__3\">The nature of the relation in respect to the delete\n                constraint. The used data type <code class=\"ph codeph\">ForeignKeyRuleType</code> has the following\n                definition: <div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"kia1665702915819__pre_b4c_nbr_dwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">typedef enum\n{\nRESTRICT,\nCASCADE,\nNULLIFY\n} ForeignKeyRuleType;\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529215\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529215\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "RelationshipType Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 15, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Describes the relationship between two tables. Description The RelationshipType structure is used to describe a relationship. The relations of a table are described in lists of these structures. These lists are available through the RelationshipInfoType structure. Data type definitions are available in unidbm.h located in the UnifaceAPSInstallDir\\uniface\\3gl\\include directory. Table 1. Elements Type Element Description unsigned char *RelationshipName Null-terminated name of the relationship (defined by the user). unsigned char *OneModelName Name of the application model in which the one entity resides. unsigned char *ManyModelName Name of the application model in which the many entity resides. unsigned char *RelatedEntityName Name of the related entity, as defined in the application model, that is, before entity assignment unsigned char *RelatedTableName Name of the related table after entity assignment. This name can contain the full operating system file name. The connector must parse the name, in the same way it does with uctrl->uname in modes 0, 1 and 2. int IsOverflow When IsOverflow has the value 1, it is a relation between a table and its overflow table. In other cases it has the value 0. int KeyNumber Uniface index number of the referenced key in the one table. KeyTypeType KeyType Type of referenced key in the one table. The used data type KeyTypeType has the following definition: typedef enum { PRIMARY_KEY, CANDIDATE_KEY } KeyTypeType; Copy int RIFields Number of fields in the foreign key and in the referenced key. int *RIFieldNumberList Array of RIFields field numbers. These identify the fields in the key (primary, candidate or foreign) of the current table in the relationship (that is, the table which is described by the current control block). unsigned char **RIFieldNameList Array of ‘RIFields’ pointers to null-terminated field names. These identify the fields in the key (primary, candidate or foreign) of the related table in the relationship (that is, the table which is not described by the current control block). ForeignKeyRuleType OnDelete The nature of the relation in respect to the delete constraint. The used data type ForeignKeyRuleType has the following definition: typedef enum { RESTRICT, CASCADE, NULLIFY } ForeignKeyRuleType; Copy Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}